k of wisdom.', 1207, 0), (398942, 'Truth is the vital breath of Beauty  Beauty the outward form of Truth.', 63062, 0), (398943, 'The trouble with lying and deceiving is that their efficiency depends entirely upon a clear notion of the truth that the liar and deceiver wishes to hide.', 2694, 0), (398944, 'There is at least one thing more brutal than the truth  and that is the consequence of saying less than the truth.', 63063, 0), (398945, 'The real gift of love is self disclosure.', 5957, 0), (398946, 'We only really face up to ourselves when we are afraid.', 1801, 0), (398947, 'It takes a lot of courage to show your dreams to someone else.', 152, 0), (398948, 'It takes more courage to reveal insecurities than to hide them  more strength to relate to people than to dominate them  more "manhood" to abide by thought-out principles rather than blind reflex. Toughness is in the soul and spirit  not in muscles and an immature mind.', 63064, 0), (398949, 'I have often though morality may perhaps consist solely in the courage of making a choice.', 63065, 0), (398950, 'Introversion  at least if extreme  is a sign of mental and spiritual immaturity.', 442, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (398951, 'The highest courage is to dare to appear to be what one is.', 45290, 0), (398952, 'It isn''t for the moment you are stuck that you need courage  but for the long uphill climb back to sanity and faith and security.', 1407, 0), (398953, 'True courage is not the brutal force of vulgar heroes  but the firm resolve of virtue and reason.', 2606, 0), (398954, 'Greatness  in the last analysis  is largely bravery-courage in escaping from old ideas and old standards.', 63066, 0), (398955, 'The highest courage is not to be found in the instinctive acts of men who risk their lives to save a friend or slay a foe  the physical fearlessness of a moment or an hour is not to be compared with immolation of months or years for the sake of wisdom or art.', 63067, 0), (398956, 'I have met brave women who are exploring the outer edge of human possibility  with no history to guide them  and with a courage to make themselves vulnerable that I find moving beyond words.', 1739, 0), (398957, 'Valour is nobleness of the mind.', 33, 0), (398958, 'Courage ... is nothing less than the power to overcome danger  misfortune  fear  injustice  while continuing to affirm inwardly that life  with all its sorrows  is good  that everything is meaningful  even if in a sense beyond our understanding  and that there is always tomorrow.', 1649, 0), (398959, 'This is the art of courage: to see things as they are and still believe that the victory lies not with those who avoid the bad  but those who taste  in living awareness  every drop of the good.', 63068, 0), (398960, 'God grant me the courage not to give up what I think is right  even though I think it is hopeless.', 63069, 0), (398961, 'The great virtue in life is real courage that knows how to face facts and live beyond them.', 178, 0), (398962, 'Physical courage  which despises all danger  will make a man brave in one way  and moral courage  which despises all opinion  will make a man brave in another. The former would seem most necessary for the camp  the latter for the council  but to constitute a great man  both are necessary.', 432, 0), (398963, 'Courage is the power to let go of the familiar.', 14621, 0), (398964, 'Valor is stability  not of legs and arms  but of courage and the soul.', 663, 0), (398965, 'One of man''s finest qualities is described by the simple word "guts"-the ability to take it. If you have the discipline to stand fast when your body wants to run  if you can control your temper and remain cheerful in the face of monotony or disappointment  you have "guts" in the soldiering sense.', 62707, 0), (398966, 'Whatever course you decide upon  there is always someone to tell you that you are wrong. There are always difficulties arising which tempt you to believe that your critics are right. To map out a course of action and follow it to an end requires ... courage.', 760, 0), (398967, 'Courage is more than standing for a firm conviction. It includes the risk of questioning that conviction.', 63070, 0), (398968, 'The hallmark of courage in our age of conformity is the capacity to stand on one''s convictions-not obstinately or defiantly (these are gestures of defensiveness  not courage) nor as a gesture of retaliation  but simply because these are what one believes.', 2467, 0), (398969, 'Courage is what it takes to stand up and speak  courage is also what it takes to sit down and listen.', 33, 0), (398970, 'The greatest test of courage on earth is to bear defeat without losing heart.', 1980, 0), (398971, 'Courage is to take hard knocks like a man when occasion calls.', 62134, 0), (398972, 'You don''t develop courage by being happy in your relationships everyday. You develop it by surviving difficult times and challenging adversity.', 28913, 0), (398973, 'This is courage ... to bear unflinchingly what heaven sends.', 542, 0), (398974, 'Courage  in the final analysis  is nothing but an affirmative answer to the shocks of existence.', 63071, 0), (398975, 'Courage is a perfect sensibility of the measure of danger  and a mental willingness to endure it.', 62938, 0), (398976, 'To have courage for whatever comes in life-everything lies in that.', 2751, 0), (398977, 'To accept whatever comes  regardless of the consequences  is to be unafraid.', 1931, 0), (398978, 'The test of courage comes when we are in the minority.', 29211, 0), (398979, 'One man with courage makes a majority.', 2245, 0), (398980, 'Many women miss their greatest chance of happiness through a want of courage in a decisive moment.', 63072, 0), (398981, 'We must have the courage to be happy.', 4754, 0), (398982, 'There is a courage of happiness as well as a courage of sorrow.', 2006, 0), (398983, 'Happy the man who ventures boldly to defend what he holds dear.', 782, 0), (398984, 'All happiness depends on courage and work.', 143, 0), (398985, 'There is nothing in the world so much admired as a man who knows how to bear unhappiness with courage.', 62237, 0), (398986, 'We must have courage to bet on our ideas  on the calculated risk  and to act. Everyday living requires courage if life is to be effective and bring happiness.', 1572, 0), (398987, 'Faint heart never won fair lady.', 62284, 0), (398988, 'The last thing a woman will consent to discover in a man whom she loves  or on whom she simply depends  is want of courage.', 1241, 0), (398989, 'None but the brave deserve the fair.', 8695, 0), (398990, 'Fortune and love favor the brave.', 782, 0), (398991, 'The bravest are the tenderest. The loving are the daring.', 147, 0), (398992, 'The weapon of the brave is in his heart.', 33, 0), (398993, 'The guts carry the feet  not the feet the guts.', 62284, 0), (398994, 'I am not afraid of a fight  I have to do my duty  come what may.', 4456, 0), (398995, 'War is fear cloaked in courage.', 63073, 0), (398996, 'A bold heart is half the battle.', 33, 0), (398997, 'Courage in danger is half the battle.', 62134, 0), (398998, 'A man of courage never wants weapons.', 33, 0), (398999, 'A brave arm makes a short sword long.', 33, 0), (399000, 'Courage which goes against military expediency is stupidity  or  if it is insisted upon by a commander  irresponsibility.', 63074, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (399001, 'There is  in addition to a courage with which men die  a courage by which men must live.', 1680, 0), (399002, 'Where life is more terrible than death  it is the truest valor to dare to live.', 63075, 0), (399003, 'The courage we desire and prize is not the courage to die decently  but to live manfully.', 3061, 0), (399004, 'Often the test of courage is not to die  but to live.', 63076, 0), (399005, 'He who has the courage to laugh is almost as much the master of the world as he who is ready to die.', 7895, 0), (399006, 'Life shrinks or expands in proportion to one''s courage.', 23, 0), (399007, 'Only those are fit to live who are not afraid to die.', 62961, 0), (399008, 'Sometimes even to live is an act of courage.', 62237, 0), (399009, 'To say yes  you have to sweat and roll up your sleeves and plunge both hands into life up to the elbows. It is easy to say no  even if saying no means death.', 713, 0), (399010, 'Have the courage to live. Anyone can die.', 63077, 0), (399011, 'Because a fellow has failed once or twice or a dozen times  you don''t want to set him down as a failure till he''s dead or loses his courage-and that''s the same thing.', 23136, 0), (399012, 'What is more mortifying than to feel that you have missed the plum for want of courage to shake the tree?', 1014, 0), (399013, 'Yesterday I dared to struggle. Today I dare to win.', 63078, 0), (399014, 'To persevere  trusting in what hopes he has  is courage. The coward despairs.', 542, 0), (399015, 'It takes vision and courage to create- it takes faith and courage to prove.', 62438, 0), (399016, 'Whatever you do  you need courage. ... To map out a course of action and follow it to an end requires some of the same courage which a soldier needs.', 760, 0), (399017, 'Who dares nothing  need hope for nothing.', 62240, 0), (399018, 'Have the courage of your desire.', 62242, 0), (399019, 'To see what is right  and not do it  is want of courage.', 819, 0), (399020, 'No great thing conies to any man unless he has courage.', 63079, 0), (399021, 'Great things are done more through courage than through wisdom.', 5058, 0), (399022, 'Courage permits the caliber of performance to continue at its peak  until the finish line is crossed.', 63080, 0), (399023, 'Failure is only postponed success as long as courage "coaches" ambition. The habit of persistence is the habit of victory.', 63081, 0), (399024, 'Courage and perseverance have a magical talisman  before which difficulties disappear  and obstacles vanish into air.', 1859, 0), (399025, 'There are a lot of fellas with all the ability it takes to play in the major leagues  but... they always get stuck in the minor leagues because they haven''t got the guts to make the climb.', 63082, 0), (399026, 'Where there is a brave man  in the thickest of the fight  there is the post of honor.', 1049, 0), (399027, 'It takes as much courage to have tried and failed as it does to have tried and succeeded.', 1407, 0), (399028, 'You will never do anything in this world without courage.', 14092, 0), (399029, 'Whenever you see a successful business  someone once made a courageous decision.', 37852, 0), (399030, 'Courage to start and willingness to keep everlasting at it are the requisites for success.', 63083, 0), (399031, 'One of the biggest factors in success is the courage to undertake something.', 63084, 0), (399032, 'Everyone has a talent. What is rare is the courage to follow that talent to the dark place where it leads.', 405, 0), (399033, 'The world is not perishing for the want of clever or talented or well-meaning men. It is perishing for the want of men of courage and resolution.', 23094, 0), (399034, 'Talent is helpful in writing  but guts are absolutely necessary.', 3164, 0), (399035, 'Knowledge without courage is sterile.', 1255, 0), (399036, 'To create one''s own world in any of the arts takes courage.', 1944, 0), (399037, 'Courage is the thing. All goes if courage