ce.', 63128, 0), (399250, 'For what avail the plough or sail  Or land  or life  if freedom fail?', 760, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (399251, 'Ay  call it holy ground  The soil where first they trod  They have left unstained  what there they found  -  Freedom to worship God.', 62925, 0), (399252, 'In the beauty of the lilies Christ was born across the sea  With a glory in His bosom that transfigures you and me  As He died to make men holy  let us die to make men free  While God is marching on.', 16036, 0), (399253, 'I am for freedom of religion and against all maneuvers to bring about a legal ascendancy of one sect over another.', 1207, 0), (399254, 'And ye shall know the truth  and the truth shall make you free.', 5587, 0), (399255, 'Those who deny freedom to others deserve it not for themselves and under a just God cannot long retain it.', 1012, 0), (399256, '... That this nation  under God  shall have a new birth of freedom.', 1012, 0), (399257, 'Since the general civilization of mankind I believe there are more instances of the abridgement of the freedom of the people by gradual and silent encroachments of those in power than by violent and sudden usurpations.', 2514, 0), (399258, 'The only freedom which deserves the name is that of pursuing our own good in our own way  so long as we do not attempt to deprive others of theirs or impede their efforts to obtain it.', 1880, 0), (399259, 'We must be free or die  who speak the tongue That Shakespeare spake  the faith and morals hold Which Milton held.', 2063, 0), (399260, 'No amount of political freedom will satisfy the hungry masses.', 2475, 0), (399261, 'I would rather sit on a pumpkin  and have it all to myself  than to be crowded on a velvet cushion.', 1049, 0), (399262, 'I never saw a Purple Cow  I never hope to see one: But I can tell you  anyhow I''d rather see than be one.', 63129, 0), (399263, 'There was an old man who said  "How Shall I flee from this horrible cow? I will sit on this stile  and continue to smile  Which may soften the heart of that cow."', 5840, 0), (399264, 'The reality is that changes are coming. ... They must come. You must share in bringing them.', 16057, 0), (399265, 'After you''ve done a thing the same way for two years  look it over carefully. After five years  look at it with suspicion. And after ten years  throw it away and start all over.', 63130, 0), (399266, 'All that philosophers have done is interpret the world in different ways. It is our job to change it.', 1336, 0), (399267, 'Christians are supposed not merely to endure change  nor even to profit by it  but to cause it.', 51228, 0), (399268, 'If you have no will to change it  you have no right to criticize it.', 33, 0), (399269, 'Changes are not predictable  but to deny them is to be an accomplice to one''s own unnecessary vegetation.', 30206, 0), (399270, 'We must learn to view change as a natural phenomenon-to anticipate it and to plan for it. The future is ours to channel in the direction we want to go ... we must continually ask ourselves  "What will happen if ... ?" or better still  "How can we make it happen?"', 63131, 0), (399271, 'One must change one''s tactics every ten years if one wishes to maintain one''s superiority.', 1702, 0), (399272, 'New things cannot come where there is no room.', 63132, 0), (399273, 'The important thing is this: to be able at any moment to sacrifice what we are for what we could become.', 7239, 0), (399274, 'When patterns are broken  new worlds emerge.', 63133, 0), (399275, 'One must lose one''s life in order to find it.', 1407, 0), (399276, 'This Mouse must give up one of his Mouse ways of seeing things in order that he may grow.', 63134, 0), (399277, 'Compromise  if not the spice of life  is its solidity.', 4867, 0), (399278, 'The only alternative to war is peace and the only road to peace is negotiations.', 12971, 0), (399279, 'Every one should keep a mental wastepaper basket and the older he grows the more things he will consign to it-torn up to irrecoverable tatters.', 4111, 0), (399280, 'Unless one says goodbye to wh