295, 'It is best to learn as we go  not go as we have learned.', 63138, 0), (399296, 'Those interested in perpetuating present conditions are always in tears about the marvelous past that is about to disappear  without having so much as a smile for the young future.', 477, 0), (399297, 'I will not change just to court popularity.', 1945, 0), (399298, 'Innovation! One cannot be forever innovating. I want to create classics.', 111, 0), (399299, 'Have no fear of change as such and  on the other hand  no liking for it merely for its own sake.', 60517, 0), (399300, 'If you want to stand out  don''t be different  be outstanding.', 63139, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (399301, 'The main dangers in this life are the people who want to change everything ... or nothing.', 63140, 0), (399302, 'To change and to improve are two different things.', 5058, 0), (399303, 'Our fathers valued change for the sake of its results  we value it in the act.', 62853, 0), (399304, 'We must beware of needless innovations  especially when guided by logic.', 3621, 0), (399305, 'All change is not growth  as all movement is not forward.', 28903, 0), (399306, 'Just because everything is different doesn''t mean anything has changed.', 63141, 0), (399307, 'None are happy but by the anticipation of change. The change itself is nothing  when we have made it  the next wish is to change again.', 2087, 0), (399308, 'We accept the verdict of the past until the need for change cries out loudly enough to force upon us a choice between the comforts of further inertia and the irksomeness of action.', 3040, 0), (399309, 'To some will come a time when change itself is beauty  if not heaven.', 7938, 0), (399310, 'Today is not yesterday  how can our works and thoughts  if they are always to be the fittest  continue always the same? Change  indeed  is painful  yet ever needful.', 3061, 0), (399311, 'Security can only be achieved through constant change  through discarding old ideas that have outlived their usefulness and adapting others to current facts.', 3784, 0), (399312, 'You had better be ready to change your mind when needed.', 63142, 0), (399313, 'Loyalty to petrified opinion never yet broke a chain or freed a human soul.', 286, 0), (399314, 'They were so strong in their beliefs that there came a time when it hardly mattered what exactly those beliefs were  they all fused into a single stubbornness.', 43, 0), (399315, 'We are chameleons  and our partialities and prejudices change place with an easy and blessed facility.', 286, 0), (399316, 'Our firmest convictions are apt to be the most suspect  they mark our